gomodel:SYNGO_2330  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"SALM3 and SALM5 expressed in nonneural cells induce presynaptic differentiation in contacting axons\"\nFig.2: \"SALM3 and SALM5 induce excitatory and inhibitory presynaptic protein clustering\"\nFig.3: \"SALM3 and SALM5 induce the uptake of synaptotagmin lumenal domain antibodies in contacting axons of cocultured neurons\"\nFig.5: \"Overexpression of SALM3 and SALM5 in cultured neurons increases the amount of presynaptic contacts\"\nFig.6: \"Overexpression of SALM3 and SALM5 in cultured neurons increases the amount of excitatory and inhibitory presynaptic contacts\". Experimental description: Dissociated culture is of rat species: \"Primary hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryonic day 18 rat hippocampi. \"\n\n15/01/2018 Pim\n- Overexpressed SALM5 is of mouse species: \"Full-length human SALM1 (aa 1-788), rat SALM2 (aa 1-766), mouse SALM3 (aa 1-636), mouse SALM4 (aa 1-626), and mouse SALM5 (aa 1-719) were subcloned into pEGFP-N1 vector (Clontech).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2018-01-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2330" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
